cs.GT, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS

The paper presents a recommender system that uses game-theoretic algorithms and machine learning techniques to match job-seekers with employers in a privacy-oriented manner. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the following sub-categories:

- cs.GT (Computer Science > Computer Science and Game Theory): The paper uses game-theoretic algorithms to generate stable pairings between employers and job-seekers, which is a central topic in this sub-category.
- cs.IR (Computer Science > Information Retrieval): The paper deals with the problem of recommending job matches to users based on their partial preferences, which is a classic information retrieval problem.
- cs.LG (Computer Science > Machine Learning): The paper proposes novel solutions that rely on machine learning techniques to improve the performance of the recommender system.
- cs.AI (Computer Science > Artificial Intelligence): The paper presents an intelligent system that can learn from user preferences and generate personalized recommendations.
- cs.DS (Computer Science > Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes adaptations of the Gale-Shapley deferred-acceptance algorithm to address the shortcomings of the original algorithm when applied to a job market.
